From 7b29fef9ff1109003ad538d0a0be68c71d784255 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcos <marcosbrendonaz@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 2026 00:27:10 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 09/14] feat: --chameleon-pierce with isolated world protection
 + Turnstile auto-click

Pierce shadow DOM and cross-origin access now only works in isolated worlds
(CDP/DevTools/Selenium), never in main world JS. This prevents fingerprinting
services from detecting the bypass.

- element.cc: OpenShadowRoot() checks DOMWrapperWorld::IsMainWorld() before
  exposing closed shadow roots
- binding_security.cc: cross-origin bypass only in isolated worlds
- chameleon_autoclick: auto-clicks Turnstile checkbox when --chameleon-pierce
  is active, runs inside the iframe renderer process (no cross-origin needed)
- Reorganized tests into tests/e2e/ with shared conftest.py helper
- Removed old test scripts from project root

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
